All services can use a filter class. If request has a baggage field, filter concats -&gt; and appRoute of current service. If there is no baggage field, filter sets appRoute of current service.

For example;
&lt;br&gt;
if A calls B and B calls C :
&lt;br&gt;
*A service output:*
&lt;br&gt;
Route=A
&lt;br&gt;
*B service output:*
&lt;br&gt;
Route=A-&gt;B
&lt;br&gt;
*C service output:*
Route:A-&gt;B-&gt;C
&lt;br&gt;

application.yaml file for A service:
-----------------------
    spring:
      application:
        name: A-service
      sleuth:
        baggage:
          remote-fields: app-route
          correlation-enabled: true
          correlation-fields: app-route
    system:
      app-route:
       name: A
Other services system.app-route.name value could be B and C

Configuration for injecting BaggageField
------------------------------------------
    @Configuration
    public class SleuthConfiguration {

         @Bean
         BaggageField appRouteField() {
            return BaggageField.create(&quot;app-route&quot;);
         }
    }

Filter class for all services:
------------------------------------------
    public class LogFilter implements Filter {

    @Autowired
    private BaggageField appRouteBaggageField;

    @Value(value = &quot;${system.app-route.name:}&quot;)
    private String appRouteName;

    @Value(value = &quot;${spring.application.name:-}&quot;)
    private String applicationName;

    private String appName;

    @Override
    public void init(FilterConfig filterConfig) {
        appName = (appRouteName == null || appRouteName.isEmpty()) ? applicationName : appRouteName;
    }

    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest servletRequest, ServletResponse servletResponse, FilterChain filterChain) {
        updateAppRouteBaggageField();
        logger.info(&quot;Route={}&quot;,appRouteBaggageField.getValue());
    }

    private void updateAppRouteBaggageField() {
        String appRouteBaggageFieldValue = appRouteBaggageField.getValue();
        appRouteBaggageField.updateValue((appRouteBaggageFieldValue == null || appRouteBaggageFieldValue.isEmpty())
                ? appName : (appRouteBaggageFieldValue + &quot;-&gt;&quot; + appName));
    }
    }

